://www.disabled-world.com/calculators-charts/convert-stones.php#footnote">I=
nsights, Updates</a></p><p><span id=3D"summary" class=3D"ltred">Synopsis:</=
span> This page provides a user-friendly weight calculator and printable ch=
art for converting measurements from stones to pounds, kilograms, and ounce=
s. It is particularly useful for individuals in regions where the stone is =
still a common unit of measure, like the United Kingdom (UK) and Ireland, a=
nd sometimes in parts of the Commonwealth, like Australia and New Zealand, =
helping to quickly and accurately convert weights for health, fitness, or d=
aily life purposes. The tool enhances understanding by offering conversions=
 in both directions, thus bridging the gap between imperial and metric syst=
ems, which can be especially helpful in medical contexts, international com=
munication, or when dealing with diverse measurement standards - <i>Disable=
d World (DW)</i>.</p><h2 id=3D"intro">Introduction</h2></div><h3>What is a =
Stone in Weight Measurement?</h3>
<p>The stone (st) is a unit of measure equal to 14 pounds (lb) or 6.3503 ki=
lograms (kg). The plural of stone is also stone. The stone measurement rema=
ins widely used in Britain, Australia, and Ireland for measuring human body=
 weight. In the U.K., Australia, New Zealand, and Ireland, people may be sa=
id to weigh, e.g., "11 stone 4" (11 stones and 4 pounds), rather than "72 k=
ilograms", or "158 pounds", as in the United States (US). Many scales today=
 provide a "change weight display" setting that you can select to display e=
ither kilograms, pounds, or stone/pounds.</p>
<p>Quick Stone Conversions:</p>
<ul>
<li>1 stone =3D 14 pounds</li>
<li>1 stone =3D 6.35029318 kilograms</li>
<li>To convert kilograms to stones, divide by 6.35029318</li>
<li>To convert stones to kilograms, multiply by 6.35029318</li>
</ul><div class=3D"spads"><ins class=3D"adsbygoogle" style=3D"display: bloc=
